caption: Excellent, fun, Hawaiian-inspired drinks. Can’t wait to come back for more drinks. Will try the food at my next visit.
Waste of time and money. Terrible food, mediocre cocktails. Overpriced. It was an overall disappointing experience. Our waitress was very kind, and that was the only plus.

My boyfriend and I were walking around looking for a place to have drinks. We walked up to the door. A man came up to the entrance and just stood there looking at us. After an awkward moment, he asked, "what are you getting?" My boyfriend said we wanted to get some drinks. The man gave a weird chuckle and said that we weren't allowed to just have drinks. We had to buy food too. My boyfriend asked if he was kidding because of his weird demeanor. The man said no. We left. I then started to read other people's reviews. I am so glad we didn't dine there. It would have been a worse experience if we did.
Really nice waiter and good experience!
Best place ever.
They have good drinks, and the service is prompt. The garlic shrimp are flavorless. Judging from the calamari/fish/shrimp plate I had, they don't know how to fry seafood; overcooked rubber

Came upon Lava Tube while meandering around Kuhio. We were stoked to find a non-resort-type bar! Their drink menu is stocked with island cocktails - read: sweet. Mai-tai it is! I love everything about this bar the way I love dive bars in general. This one is the islands version.  The gentleman (mostly bartending) and lady were cheery hosts. We weren't hungry for a meal, but we got the spicy poke to pick on as we drank. It was ono! We asked what the spicy dressing was, but they weren't letting on.  I think I will make it a point to add this spot as another stop whenever in Honolulu.
Love this place!

One of my favorite spots to enjoy aperitivos, post-meal drinks or even indulge in their food options.  Chicken tenders were delicious.  Be aware... the Adios Hawaii is the strongest drink I have had on the island. Try it if you dare. Great assortment of drink options. The staff here are AWESOME! Some of the most fun we have been able to have at a restaurant/ bar since covid, has been was had here. Love it!!

What an awesome little hole-in-the-wall! I was wandering around Honolulu hitting all the top bars that I found on Google Maps and happen to pass by this place. That wasn't even in the search results. But, what a cool little place. Great Nicole are great drink prices and a good and the prices were very reasonable!
Great service food was ok. Dinner plate was ok. Appetizer was much better than diner plate for only 2 dollars less and much better portion.
It's a good place to hang out with friends and have good drinks and have fun ... the drinks are excellent and the service people are great, I had a lot of fun ...

I like other came across this hidden gem by accident and I don't regret it. They have amazing hospitality and the prices are great. I got a pina colada made in a pineapple and it was absolutely delicious. The calamari and the spicy garlic shrimp were my favorite. Will definitely go back next time we are in Waikiki.

We were looking for a place for dinner near our condo and found this place. I read the reviews the most recent weren’t too great but they had good reviews 3 weeks ago. We decided to see for ourselves. We were quickly seated. That was about the end of the good with the exception to the nice man seated at the next table. The interior seemed run down but clean. The food..... was a NO thank you. I ordered the garlic shrimp. It comes with the shell on and with rice. The rice was from earlier in the day... dry and starting to get that texture old rice gets. The shrimp was salty and did not have a garlic flavor. We also ordered the 4.99 maitai’s, and nothing special there, but for 4.99 can’t expect much more than that. I’m always looking for local small businesses because I run one myself. I know how important it is to support local small business. I was sad that the bad reviews were on point. Hopefully they can figure out how to provide good food without sacrificing their business. I’m the end I still supported a small business but didn’t get a good meal or feel welcomed at all.

Ok look this place has its pros. The Mai Tai is really rather stiff and tasty. It'll say it's $5 at the door but it's really $10.  We queued up over an hour before close to grab a table. It was looking reasonably promising, but kind Abby suggested we have drinks by the pool while waiting for our table. With images of pool parties and bikinis in our minds, we were escorted to the adjacent dive motel pool which was what you mind find in a 1960s apartment building, with an empty beer can floating in it. It had a dimly lit, electric Blade Runner feel. There was no view to mention, save peering over the perimeter wall to catch a glimpse of PAIA Fish Market where we probably should've eaten instead. Resolving that, worst case, we'd get free (assuming a high-speed exfiltration) drinks out of this, we waited it out. Abby delivered, and not much later a table opened up too.  Everything is fried. Most is palatable. Nothing is good. We ordered appetizers only and regretted nearly all of it. The coconut shrimp was the standout item for not making me question life decisions.  My friend Gautam remarked that he was sad to learn that there was no magic with chicken wings - they get fried, and sauced after. We received dry fried wings with sauce on the side. I was sad to learn that the sauce comes from your typical squeeze jar. All in all it was a night of reckoning with inner demons. And outer demons. And a steep bill of fried food and Mai Tais.
We also found this place by accident-- food wasn't super special but we loved the service and $5 mai tai. I'd recommend :)
Found this place on accident and we came back every  night! We love Abby and her awesome hospitality!! Lava Tube is life.

I have quite literally never experienced better hospitality. We found this place by accident and ended up staying all night. Food and drinks are great, close to Waikiki beach, and I will be coming back every time I come to Oahu.
Fun décor, island style drinks and pupus... loved it!
Great drinks ,tasty food,  $5 Mai Tai
Great curb appeal

I would be giving this place a 5 but the lady wasn't very friendly- not sure if she was just having a bad moment. Also the bathrooms are in the hotel next door and you have to get a key which is a lil weird for me. The Mai Tai was very good and it is kinda cool to be able to drink your beverage in a coconut or pineapple while on vacation.
Good breakfast specials and nice staff.

I was having breakfast here and the food wasn't bad until I felt something scratch my foot. I thought it was my son's shoe stepping on my foot but when I looked down it was actually a rat. Needless to say I screamed so loud everyone in the restaurant looked at me and the person I was talking to on the phone was even concerned.  When the waitress came she said something like first time but offered nothing further. Well I certainly was not satisfied with that so I insisted on speaking to the owner. He was somewhat apologetic but I pretty much had to insist on a refund, which I received. Unfortunately, I certainly won't be dining there again.
Amazing friendly service, great food with vegetarian options and delicious cocktails! Super kitsch tiki atmosphere as well.
Tasty food and drinks with an awesome staff ( Sasha and Abby are the absolute best) ! Had delicious traditional Hawaiian food. Reasonably priced, especially for the location. Would recommend :)
Tasty Mai Tai's at a reasonable price!
Food poisoning from Chicken Lau Lau do not eat!!! Great looking place, very welcoming. But I was up all night sick
Quaint friendly and low prices
Skip it. Overpriced, nothing special.

Very underrated spot service is very mahalo💖 You ever heard of Giovanni's truck, squashed that go to Lava Tube for garlic shrimp you won't be disappointed I promise you that. Nice fresh out the ocean huge shrimp & seasoned with quality ingredients/lots of garlic!!😋 Why not have one or two Mai Tais' also😎🍹
Interesting decor in a quirky way. Food was really good and staff friendly

Great drinks and happy humorous staff!! Great environment. Decorations are awesome as well. Food is well priced but I’m not hungry enough at the moment to try anything. Maybe we’ll stop back a little later and try it.
Good option for a simple, reasonably priced breakfast.
Came here to try the $5 mai tai, although I’d refer to it as spiked POG. Not bad, but not an authentic mai tai.
Great food and drinks. Fun atmosphere and good prices.
Not bad. Drinks were a bit on the small side but not a rip off. Fried apps were piping hot (ha, I made a tube joke) and super tasty. Worth a stop to get away from all the upscale in the area.
Went here for giggles and orderedthe infamous chi chi I came to know from watching SouthPark. Can't stand the taste but it was a fun experience

Tasty food and big colourful cocktails. Reasonable prices. We found this place by accident. and were very glad we did. No tiki bar type decor inside - but nice and cool and a big mural painted all around the walls. Some impressive sculptures outside.  Not very busy late afternoon/early evening midweek and the service was quick.
Kitschy little tiki bar. They lure you in with $5 Mai Tais. Definitely stop in for one, they are good!
A unique place with tons of charm. The food is good and the drinks are even better...
Snobish bartender, good food though.
Food was okay. Not especially tasty but completely okay. Good for a _quick_ meal if you're hungry.

Really good food and drinks. Better deal than the rest of Waikiki.
We went at night for dinner but it’s like a pub... also there are just few people so we left..Not worthy.

Delightfully tacky I love this place drinks are strong with a pineapple ring
Neon lights, decorations inside and out, great service, good food and beachy music make this place so fun.

I love their burgers!! It was so fresh and hot I had to wait a bit to let it cool off. I ordered the bacon cheeseburger with no cheese or pickles (I know I'm weird) but they made it just how I like them! Super good and prices were way better than other places that try to charge twice as much. 10/10 recommend!

Awesome, a have to go stop, on the island.

Don’t let the kitschy decor put you off. Breakfast here was excellent straight forward diner fare served hot, fresh and fast. The coconut macadamia nut pancakes are killer.  Would include pic but ....

Turned up with the whole family on a Friday afternoon. Seated immediately, drinks came out fast and delicious! Food came out quickly and wow, coconut shrimp on another level! Sasha was incredible, can't say enough good things.

Great place the food was really good they have some real good sweet chili for those that like spicy they could bottle it and make a fortune my family had a great time treated with love and respect what more can you ask for. I highly recommend this place for all occasions.
Great dinner and drinks. Service was excellent.

A little touristy, but great drinks and good food! The decor is a little kitschy but interesting for sure. I tried the pineapple wine and a shark attack (they put maraschino juice in the straw, and when you lift it out, it looks like blood, kind of fun). I also tried their garlic fries (so good) and poke. Not that busy, which is nice, and they do a nice job of taking care of customers.

The food was disgusting.  The scrambled eggs were so under cooked they were running on the plate and the breakfast meats were so greasy all you could taste was oil.  When we first go there they tried bringing us the wrong order, despite not having even looked at a menu yet.  They also tried charging us for a drink we ordered, but never received.  WOULD NOT RECOMMEND! GO ACROSS THE STREET TO THE HIDEOUT!
This place is beautiful and fun! Well worth a visit!!
mai tai specials and cool vibe

First thing to know: Happy Hour is all day for the mai tai's and they are strong! Walked inside because I saw they had pancakes but it was past 11am and just wanted to see what it was about because the outside looks cool. WingChiu was very cool to meet and we decided to start our Hawaii trip with some drinks. He made the best mai tai's and the Tipsy Tiki was so delicious (and big)! The food was a type of perfection you wouldn't expect in such a low key place. The inside atmosphere was very fun and electric. We came back the next day for the pancakes and they were delicious as well. You MUST try out Lava Tube the next time you're in Waikiki!
Good bar food and great service. Mostly so-so overall, the outside is cool but there's not much to it besides being a small tiki bar.
very good
Excelent burger. Fries were less than good.
A great place to drink
Food and drinks were amazing. One man did try to take my menu away before I even knew what I was getting which I found rude. Aside from that this was a good experience.
This place in Waikiki has the best wings ..  Owners are so nice and friendly to all

A cool spot in the hood! Drinks were fun and menu looks great. Highly recommended for good times. Sit at the bar is the best option to connect with fellow revellers! Lots of local colour here! And very groovy tiki decor. Cheers!

Decent restaurant. Pricey as is usual for Waikiki. Good Mai Tai's but the specials are smaller than the regular menu.

This place is boss! The decor is quality tacky tiki in the best way, and the drinks are awesome! I didn't try the food but other reviews say they're great. The vibe is really chill and very very Hawaii - don't miss Lava Tube! Even if you pop in for just one drink, you won't regret it.

Hidden Gem in Waikiki! The inside is made like a volcano🌋 with lava lights! Wasn't a crowd or wait. Drink prices reasonable. Chicken wings & tenders served hot with a hot sauce that was hmmm hmm good😊  Get the real pina colada inside pineapple🍍
This place has chill vibes and the $5 Mai Tais are amazing. If you want a more vibrant environment head to cuckoo coconut for the same menu but a livelier mood.
Fun place to have a few delicious cocktails!

Sitting here right now having a $5 Mai Tai. The Bar Co-Owner Sasha is a big cat from Germany. The place is small-ish 15 small tables and a bar that fits maybe 3 big Samoans.  Its darkly lit like you expect from a Tiki Bar & the music playing from the speakers varies from oldies, rock, pop, to country. The $5 Mai Tai's are worth it, you can ask them to go a lil heavy and see if you get lucky. The coconut and pineapple drinks are made fresh in front of you.  It's really no frills but a fun stop for a few cheap cocktails. The bar is a live edge tree slat that looks like lava flow.  They serve food, that you can order to-go (looks good but I didn't eat).  It's attached to a hotel lobby so people are constantly in and out. Over all the customers I talked with were friendly and happy to chat. Good vibe and drinks for a walk in. Come in with a Aloha Attitude, check it out, and give it a try.
Great food service and many varieties of liquor

Cool little place. Will be back again soon.
The lady that works there in the morning is so cool absolutely love her she's the greatest my smoothies are perfect for breakfast

Awesome
Have eaten here 2 times since we got here so far. Love the food and the price.  The Mai Tais are amazing for $5 and the calamari was perfect! Will eat here again before we leave!

Super good! Great dinner burger and cheese fries! 🤩 Someone seriously invested in the decor and it's unique.... However the whole atmosphere is family friendly and absolutely delicious!  I had the classic burger and loved it. $10 for the meal. Husband got the spicy tuna ahi poke and said it was just ok so he knocked down the review to a 4. I was going to say 5 star for my meal.  Firend in the group got the Hawaiian burger and said he'd give a 4.5 star for his meal.  Another friend said she would give a 5 star for the service. We we're really well cared for and she checked on us frequently! Our receipt said her name was rachel. I didn't hear her when she told us .  Mai thai for $5, the group had mixed reviews for this but said they were heavy alcohol and we'll we'll the money .

We had the best time there . By far the best family run restaurant in Waikiki. The owner were there answer question about drinks and the menu . The wife was making drinks and the husband was running around crazy making sure everyone was happy . Being Jewish myself the last reviewer was so far wrong. Why would you bring that up . Come on man !!! This place rocks, great place . Relax you on vacation.

Omg we loved this place! The owners Sasha and ebby ( sorry if spelled wrong) were awesome! So inviting, nice , funny oh then there is the pet rooster Carlos even tho I heard he has 150 noise complaints is hilarious! I highly recommend this place! Best prices in town!
Best wings in Waikiki. Beautifully  tiki themed decor. I will probably be going back during our trip.

My kids were hungry at 10:00pm in Waikiki.  That's when all the restaurants close, even Ayesha Curry's International Smoke right across the street.  So into the Lava Tube we go.  It's got a Tiki bar vibe inside and out, adding to your favorite Waikiki memories.

Great little bar with a sweet mai tai mix.  Sometimes the little tucked away bars are the most cordial, this is one of them.  Mai Tai specials are $5 and a little on the sweeter side. Fun friendly service.
I highly recommend the tastey shortstack pancake breakfast in this lava tube cave style bar and restaurant next to the Aqua Ohia hotel.
Great drinks, friendly staff and sometimes drunken tourists who treat you like old friends and family.
The food was good ,the place was clean and the staff was nice.

There's a chance you've been drinking them wrong, but the bartenders here will teach you right.  The interior and exterior decor itself stands alone in unmistakable personality.
Amazing food and the atmosphere is also great,! Would suggest it highly
If you are visiting Waikiki area, you have to stop in here for a drink. Service was excellent and the owner is so nice. Really sets the tone for a fun trip. Also the theme is really unique.
